definitions.definition: Of a person : having no hair ; bald , bare , hairless .

subdefinitions.definition: ( ornithology ) Of a young bird , or ( part of) its body : having not developed feathers yet; featherless , unfledged ; hence, of other animals or their bodies: having no fur or hair; furless , hairless, unfurred . ( figurative ) Lacking life experience ; immature , inexperienced , naive ; also, of or relating to something immature or inexperienced.
examples: Those three young men are particularly callow youths.

subdefinitions.definition: ( by extension ) In the life cycle of an animal: newly born or hatched ; juvenile . ( entomology ) Synonym of teneral ( “ of certain insects or other arthropods such as spiders : lacking colour or firmness just after ecdysis ( “ shedding of the exoskeleton ” ) ” ) .

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) Of land : having no vegetation ; bare.

main_definition: Of a person : having no hair ; bald , bare , hairless .
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete ) Of land : having no vegetation ; bare.

definitions.definition: Of land : low-lying and near a river , and thus regularly submerged .

main_definition: ( Ireland ) Of land : low-lying and near a river , and thus regularly submerged .
